{
  "text": "With a prevalence of 0.2-1.4%, primary Sjogren's syndrome (pSS) is one of the most common chronic, slowly progressing systemic autoimmune diseases. Its main symptoms are kerato-conjunctivitis sicca and xerostomia. The extremely various clinical picture is characterized by multiple extraglandular manifestations (EGMs) and associated diseases. The women accounting for 90% of all cases in pSS. The onset age in 30-60 years. However, both distributions by age and by sex show geographical and ethnic differences [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
  "correct_citation": {
